To install:

Ensure you choose the version that matches your Mac's processor:
- Apple Silicon (M1, M2, M3, M4): Use aarch64 or arm64 downloads.

Intel Mac: Use x64 or x86_64 downloads.

Download Links:

- Temurin JDK: Adoptium MacOS Releases. Download the .tar.gz. [ https://www.google.com/search?q=https://adoptium.net/en-GB/temurin/releases%3Fos%3Dmac ]

Note: Unpack this into your jvm/ folder. On Mac, the internal folder structure usually ends in .../Contents/Home.

- Scala CLI: Scala CLI GitHub Releases.[ https://github.com/VirtusLab/scala-cli/releases ]

Apple Silicon: scala-cli-aarch64-apple-darwin.gz

Intel: scala-cli-x86_64-apple-darwin.gz

Action: Unpack, rename to scala-cli, move to your project bin/ folder.

Run the following to dequarantine downloads:
[
# Allow the Scala CLI binary to run
chmod +x bin/scala-cli
xattr -d com.apple.quarantine bin/scala-cli

# Allow the Java binaries to run (recursively for the whole JDK folder)
xattr -rd com.apple.quarantine jvm/jdk-25.0.1+8
]

- Run launch.sh to install in local env [

#!/bin/zsh

# Get the absolute path of the project directory
BASE_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" &> /dev/null && pwd)"

# Set JAVA_HOME (Note the /Contents/Home suffix common on macOS JDKs)
export JAVA_HOME="$BASE_DIR/jvm/jdk-25.0.1+8/Contents/Home"

# Prepend local bin and java to the PATH
export PATH="$BASE_DIR/bin:$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH"

echo "---------------------------------------"
echo "Scala Portable Environment Loaded (macOS)!"
echo "---------------------------------------"
echo "Java Home: $JAVA_HOME"
echo ""

# Verify binaries
java -version
echo ""
scala-cli --version
echo "---------------------------------------"

# Start a new sub-shell (Mac uses zsh by default)
exec $SHELL

], making sure to make it executable : chmod +x launch.sh

- To build: scala-cli --power package projects/web_app/app.sc --assembly -o app.jar --force
- To run: java -jar app.jar --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080
